<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861224-0141 </DOCNO><HL> M/A-Com Gets a Satellite Pact</HL><DD> 12/24/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MAI </IN><DATELINE> BURLINGTON, Mass.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   M/A-Com Inc. said it received a multimilllion-dollar contract to provide a satellite-telecommunications system to closely held Houston International Teleport.    M/A-Com, a maker of microwave and other telecommunications equipment, said Houston International will lease communications capability to corporate customers who will be equipped with small earth stations made by M/A-Com. M/A-Com has installed a hub in Houston for Houston International's satellite network. </TEXT></DOC>